SIMPLE: subdivide
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subdivide
<hw>Sub`di*vide"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Subdivided</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Subdividing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>subdividere</ets>, <ets>sub</ets> under + <ets>dividere</ets> to
divide. See <er>Divide</er>.]</ety> <def>To divide the parts of
(anything) into more parts; to part into smaller divisions; to divide
again, as what has already been divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The progenies of Cham and Japhet swarmed into colonies, and those
colonies were <qex>subdivided</qex> into many others.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subdivide</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Subdivide
<hw>Sub`di*vide"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be, or to become,
subdivided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subdivine</ent>⟦br⟧
